args:
The prince meets with Zethia and Leonidas
once again, and learns the Founder King
sacrificed himself to seal away the Other
some 300 years ago. Hoping to save Alberius,
the party delves ever deeper into the ruins.
Mars is my brother Leonidas's pactwyrm,\nwhich means he must be here as well.
I sense a ferocious flow of mana.\nThey may be engaged in battle.
Aether link system opened!\nAll iso-space connections established!\nMana plug inserted!
All locks released!\nNow, Mars! Full alchemical burst!
Not even a twitched eyebrow, eh?
You seem rather calm, given that I\nnegated an attack into which you\npoured all of your strength.

I know better than to underestimate you.
The alchemy infused into this dragon and
the otherworldly power within myself both
stem from the same sources...
Sources which you are closer to.\nThe power I possess will not defeat you.
Yet you still challenge me? Ha ha ha!\nThis attitude truly befits a crown prince.
Your drive and ambition know no bounds,\nand you do not balk at violating taboos.\nOh yes. I like you very much indeed.
Then would you seek to care for me\nas you might look after a beloved pet?\nThat is quite an honor indeed.
Aaah ha ha! I fear your soft words are\nnegated by the bloodlust in your eyes.
And while this is as good a place as any\nfor a showdown, I do not believe that\nyou and I are enemies at all.
Heh. Perhaps not. At least not until I free\nthis world from its ancient rule.
Then why don't you and I... Ah, but there's\nno need for us to rush to conclusion.\nFirst, we must greet our new guests!
Welcome, descendant of Alberius!\nOh, but I DO love a good family reunion.
Speaking of which, the great king into\nwhom you placed so much hope is\nwaiting for you even now.
I wager it is reacting to the\ndragonblood in Zethia.
Look well upon this, all of you!\nBehold the final days of your hero!
The final portion of the Other's flesh\nought to be here...
By the goddess, is THAT the core of the\nOther?! But how was it not destroyed\nwhen the soul was sealed away?
Morsayati?! Where are you?!\nShow yourself, fiend!
You ought to know where I am, mortal.\nYou sealed me away, after all.
You're in my bodyâ€”no, my blood.
Yes. The soul within your blood awoke\nwhen you stood before my body.
So even though I sealed away your soul,\nyour body still yet lives...
I would not expect an insect such as\nyourself to understand my magnitude.
Even without a soul, my body still\npossesses the strength to lay waste\nto your entire kingdom.
I must put an end to this,\nno matter the cost!
And how will you do this, human?\nYour beloved holy blade is destroyed,\nand I now exist in your very blood!
You cannot defeat me, so why resist?\nOffer your flesh unto me, human!\nBecome the cornerstone of my rebirth!
Never! This body is still my own!
You are an amalgamation of pure power.\nI will absorb that power and contain it!
What arrogance! Your pathetic flesh sac\ncould never hope to contain me!
You know as well as I that would curse\nyou as well, Chthonius.
My will is ever with you, my king.

It saddens me beyond measure to do
this, old friend, but I see no other way...
So by the power and honor of our pact,
lend your strength to me one last time!
S-such miasma... But I must hold fast...\nI must absorb it all!
N-now, Morsayati... You and I shall rest...\nin the depths of the earth...for all time...
Heh heh heh... You didn't honestly believe\nyou could take my power into your body\nand pay no cost for it, did you?
Such is the reward for a human who\nattempts to fill the office of a god.
Your miserable flesh cannot hold me\nin check forever! My resurrection is\nsimply a matter of time!
Nonetheless, I have bought humanity time.\nOur hopes now lie with future generations.
So that was how the Founder King\nmet his end...
Ah, it would make me wail as well to see\nthe hero in whom I placed all of my trust\nmeet such a feeble end.
There was nothing feeble about it!
Yeah, it wasn't permanent, but at least it\nkept yer miserable butt sealed away for\na few hundred years!
Alberius gave everything he had\nto bring peace to this world.
All I see is a man who lived with honor\nto his very last breath. I am proud to\ncall him my ancestor!
Aaaah ha ha ha! Will you still say that\nafter what you see next?
Hold a moment. Who was THAT?!
Clearly a dragon of some sort,\nyet the roar was so ominous...
Eeeeek! S-something is creeping up\nfrom over the precipice!
So I know I'm not the smartest guy in\nthe room, but if that's Chthonius,\ndoesn't that mean it's also...?
It seems storing the Other has not exactly\ndone wonders for his health.
He's going to attack us all! Save meeee!
Think of the strength required to hold onto\nhis humanity under such conditions...
M-my descendants... I would have you...\ngrant my final wish...
My body...and my spirit...\nare at their limits...
The Other is in the midst of his revival...\nand I can hold him back no longer.
You must...destroy me... Destroy me and\nthe beast's core...while you can!
You always WERE the chatty one, Alberius!
I wager the Other's influence\nis revitalizing the core within\nChthonius.
We're all gonna be turned into paste\nif he keeps thrashin' around in here!
He flew off... Man, talk about an exit!
And what do you intend to do\nwhen you catch up to him?!
It ain't like we got much of a choice, Cleo.
I know, Ranzal... And yet,\nI cannot fight His Majesty!
I'm not giving up hope just yet, Cleo.\nBut we'll never know if we can help him\nif we don't track him down right now!
I will never give up on His Majesty. Never!
